se.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dunkelheit>Dunkelheit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/3/02 12:33:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23581.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Revamp the zones</span><hr size=1> There are 2 things I would definitely like to be changed:<br><br>1. In the mid levels you run around and do not find a group other than in LoiO - Overthere. These zones suck. You have no chance to find a group in Paw without looking for hours.<br><br>2. In high levels places are too crowded.... Sebilis and KC e.g.<br><br>Reasons for 1:<br>People know that they can find a group in LoiO so they stay there because travelling IS an issue in low levels. I don't know who started to hunt in these sucky zones, but now we have to take it as it is.<br><br>Reasons for 2:<br>Loot is one reason for Sebi or KC... you find really useable loot there and you can get exp quite easy.<br><br>Solutions for 1:<br>take away some midlevel Dungeons... make najena or paw or nurga high level zones..... keep one or two midlevel dungeons NEAR these zones, so that peeps can take a change of pace. Put BETTER loot in the dungeon zones so that there is a motivation to hunt.<br><br>Solution for 2:<br>REVAMP all the zones.... make the loot in SolB or Guk better. What about risk vs reward? What is the point in going to the hole? Loot sucks there. What is so difficult in changing the drop tables? After this we will start seeing groups down there again. And travelling is not such a big issue. People may even go away from the boring pulling-to-one-spot-from-one-spawn tactics and make some dungeon crawling.<br><br>Make one or two zones VERY difficult for one group, but make a better exp modifier for the zone.... Some zones are 3 years old they NEED a change. <br><br>Do you have any other thoughts on this? Play game designer... what would you change? How do we get the midlevel crowd in one or 2 places? How do we make zones with nice risk vs. reward? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uviantedouxcauseur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VianteDouxCauseur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/3/02 5:32:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23581.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Revamp the zones</span><hr size=1> I think there need to be some server splits rather then more high level zones.<br><br>Sebilis, Charisis, Chardok, New Cazic Thule, Fungus Grove, Umbral, Ahkeva, The Grey, Ssra, etc...There are enough high level zones.  As for the other thing the medium level areas, there are plenty of them too.  People are just lazy, adding new zones is not the answer really.  But when you have a server with 40in seb, 40 in ME, 20in Charisis, 20 in chardok etc...There is a problem.  It's not lack of zones it is overcrowding. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugabus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gabus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/3/02 7:09:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23581.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Revamp the zones</span><hr size=1> Its the lack of people with an adventurous bend to their personality that is keeping them in DL and the lake. EQ doesnt really reward those that explore new places to them, and in fact punishes them for it.. exploration = death, exp loss, and time loss. Maybe if there was some kind of incentive for a group to pick up and move, they would go. I know when I was in the 40's and would be in a rockin group, id say &quot;lets go over to CoM and clean house!&quot; ... and the sound of crickets and tumbleweeds would roll by. Despite the fact we had a druid that could port us there, melees could bind there, there was awesome loot and exp, and we could be there by ourselves, and in no more than 10 mins. I think if the death penalty wasnt so stiff..we might see people spread out more. <br><br>What if some zones were earmarked as non-exp loss areas? That might increase the safety aspect of the zone, and not toss out the whole economy by upgrading loot, or sending the farmers scurrying there. Or, if a blue mob or lower kills you, you lose exp, but death to red mob or yellow is a lower penalty or none at all. (Since that thing outclassed you, and you have learned to stay away from it) I mean sure... ther could (and would) be s'ploiting, but I think that would balance the risk/reward aspect of it.<br><br>All too often Verant looks at the reward part of an encounter to make a change. Perhaps looking at risk would solve a whole other issue. People hunt in DL and LoIO cause it is safe. Make other areas as safe or safer, and people will move around abit.<br><br> <p><Br><center> Magelo Profiles </center> <center> <a target="new" href=" http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=139779">Gabus Copperdrachon</a> | <a target="new" href=" http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=139811">Niccollo</a> </center>   <br> <center> <a target="new" href="immortalpower.org">Immortal Power</a> </center>   <center> Rodcet Nife </center> <BR><center> Reality is for those who cannot handle fantasy. </center> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usnarkystabwell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Snarky Stabwell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/3/02 8:05:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23581.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Revamp the zones</span><hr size=1> It's a low risk vs high exp/loot reward in many of those zones that are crowded. It would take some downgrading of experience in Dreadlands/LOIO and upgrade in other areas to shift that pace.<br><br>Another good idea would be some random good items that could drop not only from boss mobs but any mob in some of the older zones to get people to go back there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udevemt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DeveMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/3/02 9:18:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23581.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Revamp the zones</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  People go to LOIO and OT for one reason.....Fast exp from seemingly an unlimited supply of mobs. OT camps were usually set up along KC walls, now that there 10-12 groups grinding, they are now in the middle of the zones.<br><br>Upgrading pop times in areas would be the easiest solution.<br><br>Deve <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uslyydaugg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Slyy Daugg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitl