ter type mobs.  These invariably more dangerous.  So trading off many of the caster mobs for melee mobs would make the zones more attractive.  Also the pathing in many of the dungeons is just horrible.  If a mob is agroed and because you backed up 2 feet to get it to follow you, it therefore wanders completely around a larger room agroing 10 other mobs, this is bad.  Fixing pathing issues would make these places more attractive.  And finally, most of them no longer have items that are significantly attractive to players.  So a loot table revamp might be in order.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uslyydaugg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Slyy Daugg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/3/02 10:29:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23581.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Revamp the zones</span><hr size=1> &quot;And finally, most of them no longer have items that are significantly attractive to players. So a loot table revamp might be in order.&quot;<br><br>I think this should be in THE NEXT PATCH .  It will go way further in soving this issue than any other IMO, and this issue is worth solving.<br><br>SD<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulordmaxwell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LordMaxwell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/9/02 1:44:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23581.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Revamp the zones</span><hr 