e an SK is their ability to solo.  I personally only hunted &quot;out doors&quot; from lvl 1-10 in Field of Bone.  Once I hit Kurn's tower (great 10-20exp, and now completely unused) I decided this is what I play this game for.  The adventure of exploring a dungeon and the risk factor involved that made me not go &quot;AFK Biobreak&quot; &quot;getting a drink&quot; &quot;letting the dog out&quot; etc. etc..  You didn't want to move from your comp, you had to be alert at all times.  When exp dried up in Kurns, I did spend 5-6 lvls in LOIO grinding out some exp.  <br><br>Then it was off to Dalnir!!  I'd been hearing so much about this zone and how much fun it was.  (This is back when Fighting Batons were all the rage, and Lumpy was camped 24/7)  Leaving Dalnir after lvl 37ish, I headed to Kaesora.  Talk about a sweet sweet zone.  VERY difficult, and great exp there too.  Again, a zone that holds your attention and gets the heart rate up.  <br><br>After spending time in Kaesora it was off to many other zones, Sol B, Nurga, Droga, City of Mist etc etc.  <br><br>Seems like everyone just wants the ho hum experience of LOIO, OT, DL, KC.  How very very boring, yet its so easy for them.  So why change?  Why go explore?  To much time is spent obsessing over &quot;I can't wait to get to X level.&quot;  Thats why I have created my Rogue.  Hopefully I'll be able to get other guild members together and go back and hunt these zones with full groups and be able to enjoy them.<br><br>And the point about learning things at lower levels is dead on.  In the Plane of Hate the other day, and I felt like I was in a dungeon with a bunch of people who wanted to pull X mob to X safe spot over and over.  No one understood tactics of the fight, people STILL didn't know how to assist, no one understood tag pulling, was a total mess and we had three complete wipe outs.  Maybe if they did something OTHER than...  Pull to FD or BD in LOIO, Pull to Ledge, Pull to North Wall, they'd have a clue what they are doing.  I know I may sound bitter, but I believe the hours of CRs and solo time in dangerous places taught me well.  I wish some of the people who are more worried about their twinks, spent more time learning the game and zone, then the stats of this weapon or that weapon in the auction zone.<br><br>So in conclusion: I think they need to do what they did to Cazic Thule to alot of the other zones.  Make people RE Learn the game and zones based on new mobs and levels.  You'd see alot more people exploring and moving around.  Land some named Dragons in LOIO and watch those /ooc and /shout bandits scatter!!!  <br><br>Sorry if I offended or upset anyone with this long drawn out post, just wanted to share some ideas and feelings.  And again, I'm new to the boards, hope to be of some help if I can!<br><br>Be Safe!<br>Merdarr<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uparticleboy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>particleboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/10/02 2:13:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23581.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rewards</span><hr size=1> /sigh, theres always one who has to accuse people of not being &quot;adventurous&quot; by hunting in DL (etc).  In doing so they completely miss the point of why people do that.  When I was in my 40s I could log on for an hour or two in DL, get a pickup group with relative ease and leave with relative ease (the group could then easily find a replacement in most cases).<br><br>Now what if I based myself in Kedge Keep instead.  I'd have a pretty long wait to find a group there.<br><br>The problem is that group structure is too rigid, people have no efficient way of finding groups across zones and people have wildly varying amounts of time that they can play.  This means a zone has to reach a critical mass of people before it becomes a good pickup zone.  This success brings in more people and if the game designers weren't careful the zone gets overcrowded.  I'm really hoping Verant's zone and game designers have picked up on this.<br><br>What I'd like to see from EQ2 is:<br><br>1. Abilities more spread around.  The &quot;enchanter abomination&quot; mistake should never be repeated (they have too many crucial abilities and often a virtually monopoly thereof);<br><br>2. A larger role for generalists in the mid to high end game; and<br><br>3. Much larger zones that can support many more people (a zone should really be able to support 100+ people comfortably as a criterion of success).<br><br>Luclin made me a bit nervous.  The zones are pretty but they're much smaller than many Kunark and Velious zones (that higher polycount doesn't come for free).  Small zones are (imho) a mistake.<br> <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=163097">Hagin Netherblade</a><br>&lt;<a href="http://www.thunder.at">Thunder</a>&gt;<br>59th level Barbarian Blackguard<br>Innoruuk Server</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showMessageRange?topicID=23581.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showMessageRange?topicID=23581.topic&start=41&stop=49>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showPrevMessage?topicID=23581.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showNextMessage?topicID=23581.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussi